            <p>Rev. Isaac P. Mendes&#44;<lb/>
                Savannah&#44; Ga.<lb/></p>
            <p>December 28<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1885<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais<lb/>
                Philadelphia Pa.<lb/>
                Rev &#38; Dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>Will you kindly inform me<lb/> whether you have ever officiated at a Jewish<lb/> Wedding with Christian Bridesmaids&#44; and<lb/> whether you think such a proceeding in<lb/> keeping with Jewish Law and Custom. Mrs<lb/> A.Minis&#91;&#63;&#93; of this city asserts that you have<lb/> done so to your own Synagogue   in Philadelphia&#44;<lb/> and has given me &#91;&#63;&#93; permission.  I use her <lb/> name in making the inquiry. I trust you<lb/> will pardon my troubling you&#44; but I would very<lb/> much like to have your opinion on this subject.<lb/></p>
            <p>With kindest  regards and best wishes.<lb/></p>
            <p>Very truly  &#38; fraternaly<sic></sic> Yours<lb/>
                Isaac P. Mendes<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
